  "prompt": "I have a Tata Indica 2007 model. Can I attach it with Ola?",
  "response": "Yes, you can attach your Tata Indica 2007 model with Ola, but there are a few factors to consider:\n\n1. **Age of the Vehicle**: Ola typically has certain age restrictions for vehicles on its platform. As of 2023, the maximum age limit for vehicles is usually around **15 years** in many regions. Since your Tata Indica is a 2007 model, it may still be eligible, but you should check the specific regulations in your city or region.\n\n2. **Condition of the Vehicle**: The car must be in good condition, both mechanically and aesthetically. Ola may require a vehicle inspection to ensure it meets their standards.\n\n3. **Documentation**: Ensure all necessary documents are up-to-date, including registration, insurance, and emission compliance (PUC certificate). Ola will require these documents for verification.\n\n4. **Registration**: The vehicle must be registered as a commercial vehicle (Yellow Plate) in most regions to operate with Ola. If it's currently registered as a private vehicle (White Plate), you may need to convert it to a commercial registration.\n\n5. **Ola's Policies**: Ola may have specific policies or preferences regarding the type of vehicles they allow on their platform. The Tata Indica is a common car in the Indian market, so it\u2019s likely acceptable, but it\u2019s best to confirm with Ola directly.\n\n### Steps to Attach Your Car to Ola:\n1. **Download the Ola Partner App** and register as a driver.\n2. Submit the required documents (driver\u2019s license, vehicle RC, insurance, PUC, etc.).\n3. Schedule a vehicle inspection if required.\n4. Once approved, you can start accepting rides.\n\nIf your car is nearing the age limit or doesn\u2019t meet Ola\u2019s requirements, you might explore other options like private rentals or local cab services. Always verify with Ola\u2019s customer support or website for the latest policies.",
